column4: Ascona Group Roadside Retail Specialists Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 2/1 Our Boy Stan, 3/1 Livingit Du Large, 4/1 Kocktail Bleu, 6/1 Bobby's Nelson, 7/1 Phineas Bunce, 8/1 Trade War, 50/1 Dixie Mafia
column36: Absent since very promising bumper debut in early 2024 but remains of interest
column37: Runner-up on Irish point debut in October 2023 and made very promising rules debut when close/clear second in heavy-ground Chepstow bumper the following January; makes hurdling debut after 649-day absence but remains of interest.

column4: Ascona Group Roadside Retail Specialists Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 2/1 Our Boy Stan, 3/1 Livingit Du Large, 4/1 Kocktail Bleu, 6/1 Bobby's Nelson, 7/1 Phineas Bunce, 8/1 Trade War, 50/1 Dixie Mafia
column36: 2-8 in points; made quite promising rules debut in March but well beaten here recently
column37: 2-8 in Irish points last year; made quite promising rules debut when staying-on fourth at Warwick (2m, good) in March but was well beaten when upped to 2m4f here (soft) 12 days ago; now drops back in trip.

column27: A Peltier, D Juste & J Houdin

column4: Ascona Group Roadside Retail Specialists Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 2/1 Our Boy Stan, 3/1 Livingit Du Large, 4/1 Kocktail Bleu, 6/1 Bobby's Nelson, 7/1 Phineas Bunce, 8/1 Trade War, 50/1 Dixie Mafia
column36: Beat next-time-out winner in junior hurdle in January and has no penalty here
column37: Built upon encouraging debut when keeping on well to win junior hurdle at Chepstow (2m, heavy) in January, form that was given a good boost by the runner-up soon afterwards; avoids a penalty here and has obvious scope for further progress this season.

column4: Ascona Group Roadside Retail Specialists Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 2/1 Our Boy Stan, 3/1 Livingit Du Large, 4/1 Kocktail Bleu, 6/1 Bobby's Nelson, 7/1 Phineas Bunce, 8/1 Trade War, 50/1 Dixie Mafia
column27: N J Henderson And Mrs S A Aston
column36: Looked useful in bumpers last season; good hurdling prospect this term
column37: Runner-up in Listed junior bumper at Cheltenham (soft) on debut in January and beat recent Persian War third Moneygarrow when going one better at Kempton (good to soft) the following month; out of a useful hurdler and looks a good prospect for the season ahead.

column4: Ascona Group Roadside Retail Specialists Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 2/1 Our Boy Stan, 3/1 Livingit Du Large, 4/1 Kocktail Bleu, 6/1 Bobby's Nelson, 7/1 Phineas Bunce, 8/1 Trade War, 50/1 Dixie Mafia
column36: Made the frame in both bumpers; nice prospect but others in this line-up appeal more
column37: Out of a half-sister to top-class chaser Master Minded; made the frame in both bumpers last season, latterly when close second of 12 at Doncaster (good; other run was on soft) in March; ought to make his mark over hurdles fairly soon but others in this line-up have more compelling form.

column4: Ascona Group Roadside Retail Specialists Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 2/1 Our Boy Stan, 3/1 Livingit Du Large, 4/1 Kocktail Bleu, 6/1 Bobby's Nelson, 7/1 Phineas Bunce, 8/1 Trade War, 50/1 Dixie Mafia
column36: Nice pedigree; only fourth when favourite for last season's bumper debut; Sean Bowen rides
column37: Half-brother to useful jumper Drumlee Sunset; unable to justify warm favouritism when only fourth of six in heavy-ground course bumper last December and not seen again since but should have a future over jumps and Sean Bowen is booked today.

column4: SIS Brown Lad Handicap Hurdle (Listed Race)

column4: SIS Brown Lad Handicap Hurdle (Listed Race)
column20: 2/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Sysko, 11/2 Backtonormal, 8/1 Sommesky, 9/1 Positive Thinker, 10/1 Pour Les Filles,  Letos,  The Nagger Reidy, 14/1 Linden Arden, 18/1 Staffordshire Knot, 25/1 Eagles Reign, 33/1 Catch The Beast, 50/1 In Excelsis Deo,  Digby

column37: Runner-up in the 2024 Fred Winter; won the Lartigue (big 4yo handicap) at Listowel last year; ended a run of poor form with Fairyhouse second over 2m6f on his final start last season; had a spin in a charity race at the Curragh in late-August; had dropped out of contention when unseating three out at Gowran last month.

column4: SIS Brown Lad Handicap Hurdle (Listed Race)

column37: Not the most dependable sort when trained by Harry Fry, though won a Grade 2 handicap chase at Cheltenham in April last year (2m4f, good); has had two runs over fences for Enda Bolger, made mistakes at Punchestown, pulled up in the Munster National; up against it on return to hurdling.

column4: SIS Brown Lad Handicap Hurdle (Listed Race)
column20: 2/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Sysko, 11/2 Backtonormal, 8/1 Sommesky, 9/1 Positive Thinker, 10/1 Pour Les Filles,  Letos,  The Nagger Reidy, 14/1 Linden Arden, 18/1 Staffordshire Knot, 25/1 Eagles Reign, 33/1 Catch The Beast, 50/1 In Excelsis Deo,  Digby

column4: SIS Brown Lad Handicap Hurdle (Listed Race)
column20: 2/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Sysko, 11/2 Backtonormal, 8/1 Sommesky, 9/1 Positive Thinker, 10/1 Pour Les Filles,  Letos,  The Nagger Reidy, 14/1 Linden Arden, 18/1 Staffordshire Knot, 25/1 Eagles Reign, 33/1 Catch The Beast, 50/1 In Excelsis Deo,  Digby
column27: E A R L Haras Du Luy
column36: Second in a 2m4f contest at Listowel on handicap debut, likely to make his presence felt
column37: 2m maiden winner on Flat in France at three; ran only once in 2024; won a 2m3f Punchestown maiden in June (gd-yld); came up short when last of seven in a Listed hurdle at Galway (16.5f, good) on latest; more like it back up in trip when second in a 2m4f contest at Listowel on handicap debut; likely to make his presence felt.

column4: SIS Brown Lad Handicap Hurdle (Listed Race)

column36: Found 2m too sharp in a Grade 2 novice race here in March, respected on overall form
column37: Trounced Custom Taylor (now a 137-rated three-time winner) in a 2m3f maiden at Limericklast Christmas; out of depth in 2m6f Grade 1 novice event at Dublin Racing Festival; found 2m too sharp in a Grade 2 novice race at this venue in March; makes handicap/seasonal debut for in-form top stable.

column32: K Haughey & Laura Haughey & Kieran T Byrne
column36: Failed to stay 3m when unplaced favourite at Cheltenham 15 days ago, could do better now
column37: Useful bumper form in 2022/23 season; seem to have had issues. opened his hurdles account with 9l win in small field at Downpatrick (2m6f, yielding) last month on first run since January; failed to stay 3m when unplaced favourite at Cheltenham 15 days ago.

column37: Ballinrobe handicap hurdle winner over 2m6f trip in May off 115 (good) before just denied in valuable 3m2f Uttoxeter handicap chase; a long way below his best in two races over hurdles last month.

column37: Better known as a staying handicap chaser; absent since beaten only a short in last year's 3m4f Cork National; previously placed off his hurdles mark at Roscommon; could go well if fit and ready to do himself justice.

column36: Ended last term on a high note, trip-versatile but realistically more of a stayer
